@article{bartos_ernest_1986,
  abstract = {The article presents an interview of Ernest Dichter, founder and president of Ernest Dichter Associates International Ltd. On asking Dichter, about his reason to get into the research field, he said that he came to the United states via Paris in 1938. His first job was in conventional market research, and what struck him, coming from clinical psychology and psychoanalytic research, was that people were being asked through questionnaires why they were buying milk, which happened to be one of the first things he worked on, and he just couldn't swallow that. It was almost comparable to asking people why they thought they were neurotic or to a physician asking a patient whatever disease he thought he had. Answering to a question as to what was his perspective and problems when he first entered the field, and how he sees the issues and problems today he said that, there have been some improvements but not enough to satisfy him. There are beautiful correlation coefficients being established which demonstrate that a particular group of people happen to be using this particular product more frequently. But then the jump is made that they are buying it because they are young, and that's where the problem arises.},
